subject: Dear Consignment Owners/Bene
body:
Dear Consignment Owners/Beneficiaries,
Dear Banking transfer of Funds Beneficiaries,
Dear Gold transactions and Cocoa transactions Beneficiaries,
Dear Crude oil and other Petroleum Contract Beneficiaries,
Dear Sir,
This is a STOP ORDER from the PARTNERS  AFRICA UNION DEVELOPMENT BANK and INTERNATIONAL BANK FOR AFRICA.
This STOP ORDER is to inform all beneficiaries to stop all transactions indefinitely.  Failure to do so will cost you more money and waste more time. The IMF/ UN / AFrican Union Act19 Sec-419. This is to avoid payments of more fees and loss of money.
This new year our banks have been Assigned to make all payments in Funds and in Gold.
NOTE: Provide your Bank details for payment.
      Provide your personal details and bank details.
      Your telephone number and whatsapp number for fast communication.
      Provide your Home Address for door to door delivery of your consignment.
      Your first payment of $25,000,000.00 for this month is ready now.
 
Best regards,
Management AUDB AND IBOA.

subject: Re:   Dear Consignment Owners/Bene
body:
Hello there,

Thank you for reaching out and sharing this information. It's quite interesting to hear about the STOP ORDER from the PARTNERS AFRICA UNION BANK and BANK FOR AFRICA. I'm curious, could you explain a bit more about what this order entails? 

Also, it's intriguing that your banks have been assigned to make all payments in Funds and Gold this new year. Could you provide more details on how this process works? 

Looking forward to hearing from you soon.

Best wishes,
Sean
